JOHANNESBURG – South African Airways (SAA) CEO Vuyani Jarana and the airline's board have walked out of Parliament, refusing to deliver a scheduled presentation. Jarana was meant to present a turnaround strategy for the airline on Wednesday. #SAA presentation before Parliament has been cancelled. It was a closed meeting over its financial results and turn around presentation. This is highly irregular. Now after MPs protested it’s been withdrawn. SAA CEO leaving the building @eNCA READ: Turbulence ahead as SAA records massive loss The SAA delegation wanted a closed meeting, but MPs objected, citing a lack of transparency. Closed meetings in Parliament are unusual. #SAA Board and CEO all walk out/ leave Parliament after its presentation was meant to be closed and MPs objected. Closed meetings in Parliamemt are unusual. pic.twitter.com/HMP1Ihxeop eNCA